{
  "texts": [
    "It also outperforms the least performing ME based system with a change of 9.5%.",
    "Patil et al. [81] demonstrated a machine learning-based statistical named entity recognition system for the identification and categorization of named entities found in Marathi language literature using CRF.",
    "They have achieved the experimental accuracy was 70.68% for recall, 75.51% for F1-measure and 82.33% for precision on FIRE-2010 corpus dataset by using CRF based on Machine learning.",
    "Jadhav and Jadhav [52] utilized Python module serval in order to assess sequence labelling which is employed to assess the effectiveness of chunking activities like posture tagging and named-entity recognition, among others.",
    "The authors have been applied the dataset named Conll2023 with Roberta tokenizers and its Roberta-base model to identify the meaningful sentences."
  ]
}